  "definitions": [
    "to whip or lash",
    "(figurative, by extension) (of a natural agent) to strike or hit violently\nle onde sferzavano la rivathe waves broke on the shore\nla grandine ha sferzato la campagnathe hail hit the countryside",
    "(figurative, by extension) to criticize harshly",
    "(figurative, by extension) to stimulate; to spur"
  ],
  "description": "sferzare (transitive)",
  "etymology": "Unknown, but possibly sferza (“whip, lash”) + -are.",
